x4freetext: 45 MeV karlsruhe isochronous cyclotron
.Deuteron burst width 1 ns, repetition rate 20 kc/s.
U(d,nx)-reaction.
Broad neutron spectrum in the energy region from
0.3 to 30 MeV.
Natural uranium with thickness 0.09542 atoms/barn.
Sample impurities were ascertained to contribute
less than 0.3%.
Time of flight path = 187.5 m.
.Overall time resolution = 5.48 nsec. (See comment)
transmission measurement.
.The neutron beam was collimated at 1 m, 10 m and 37 m
from the source to about 2.E-6 sr.
.The sample was positioned at 1.5 m from the source.
.Alternating runs with the sample in and out of the
beam on a 250 sec cycle.
proton recoil plastic scintillator,
NE102A, 25 cm diameter 1 cm thick,
viewed simultaneously by two XP-1040 phototubes.
.The resolution of 0.029 ns/m corresponds to an energy
resolution of about 290 eV at 0.5 MeV and 7.44 keV at
4.35 MeV. The purpose of this work was to perform a
high resolution total cross section measurement with
good statistics.
.More than 3000 data points were obtained and the
results are in good agreement with other data except
some older measurements.
In the sample  out  position, the average counting
rate for the detector was about 0.4 neutrons per
machine burst.
Up to 3 counts per machine burst could be accepted by
the time analyzer and data acquisition system.
Corrected for background and
for the dead time of the time recording system.
Multiple scattering effects are estimated to be
negligible.
The resolution width in the final reduced data
corresponds to 1.37 times the point spacing.
The statistical uncertainty lies
between 0.45% at 4.35 MeV and 2.58% at 0.5 MeV.
The effects of sample impurities were
ascertained to contribute less than 3% uncertainty to
the cross-section.
